Narrator

The crisp morning air filled my lungs as I crossed the palace courtyard with Hugo.

Player_Romus_Italic

I ignored the guards and continued onward.

Player_Romus_Italic

I waved halfheartedly at them as I passed.

Player_Romus_Italic

I offered a high-five by holding up my hand.

Player_Romus

"Shh! I want to see what happens."

Player_Romus

"As king, I mustn't indulge in gambling, whether with money or life."

Player_Romus

"I don't have time for this. Would you kindly get their attention?"

Player_Romus

"Your oversight is duly noted."

Player_Romus

"Agreed. There are substantial benefits to strengthening ties between us."

Hugo Toras

"I can tell you, first hand, that he's fully capable of executing them with utmost proficiency."

Hugo Toras

"But I'm getting ahead of myself. Captain Gordion can tell you more."

Hugo Toras

In this case, the potential benefits of fostering increased trust and improved coordination with the Golden Guard, would enhance your security measures and personal well-being."

Player_Romus

"I certainly hope so."

Player_Romus

"That's reassuring. However..."

Player_Romus

"If he doesn't, it may put into question the necessity of the Golden Guard."

Narrator

It wasn't long before we'd crossed the courtyard and reached the armory, which also served the Golden Guard's headquarters."

Narrator

Both seemed unsure how to react.

Player_Romus

"Don't worry, I'm granting you permission to touch me."

Player_Romus

"You're no fun... But yes. Let us continue our journey."

Narrator

We eventually reached a training facility where we found Captain Gordion in boxing gloves sparring with another Golden Guardsman.

Hugo Toras

"My money is on Captain Gordion. What do you say, 50 guilder?"

Player_Romus

"I'll take that bet."

Hugo Toras

"Right away."

Player_Romus

"I arrived sooner than anticipated. It's not your fault."

Player_Romus

"I'm surprised you were unaware of your king's whereabouts, considering that falls within your jurisdiction."

Narrator

The two men circled each other for a while before they started swinging. Three rounds later, the Captain had my guy on the ropes.

Player_Romus

"No. You take the other guy. *My* money is on Captain Gordion."

Hugo Toras

"It appears Captain Gordion has emerged victorious."

Player_Romus

"It certainly appears that way. Looks like I owe you."

Titus Gordion

"Your Majesty! Many apologies. I didn't see you there. You're earlier than I expected."

Player_Romus

"Alright, enough chit-chat. Let's get out of here and talk somewhere more private."

Narrator

The two men circle each other for a while before they began exchanging swings. Three rounds later, the Captain had Hugo's guy in a tight spot.

Hugo Toras

"It appears Titus has emerged victorious. Looks like I owe you."

Hugo Toras

"Tempting, but no thanks. I've already lost once today. Don't need a repeat."

Titus Gordion

"No need, but I appreciate the sentiment. I was just showing our newest recruit a thing or two in the ring."

Titus Gordion

"Of, course."

Hugo Toras

"Yes, Your Majesty."

Narrator

As the two men circled each other, we observed their careful dance before they engaged in combat. Although the other fighter managed to land a few hits, the match concluded with Captain Gordion prevailing, thanks to a powerful punch to his opponent's jaw.

Player_Romus_Italic

I lightly applauded his win.

Player_Romus

"Bravo!"

Titus Gordion

"Courtesy of my former boxing days."

Titus Gordion

"Complementary of professional boxing day."

Hugo Toras

"Well, Your Grace... Shall we?"

Player_Romus

"Thanks, but your council is no longer required. I'd like to speak to the captain alone."

Player_Romus

"Good. Now get to it."

Hugo Toras

"I see. Well, if that is your wish, I will stay where I am."

Hugo Toras

"After you, Your Grace."

Hugo Toras

"If you want to ensure the good captain is on our side, then yes. We 'must.'"

Narrator

Hugo seemed to force a smile before bowing his head and turning away.

Hugo Toras

"Very well, then."

Hugo Toras

"As you command."

Hugo Toras

"Yes. Understood."

Narrator

Hugo and I caught up to Titus as he was stepping inside the building.

Narrator

Upon entering, we were once again enveloped by an array of antiquated weaponry and armor.

Hugo Toras

"I've always loved this old stuff."

Narrator

Titus motioned toward the displays.

Titus Gordion

"I brought most of this out of storage soon after I took command. A considerable portion of what you see was in bad shape and required extensive refurbishment."

Hugo Toras

"Ha! As long as we get the green light from animal rights activists!"

Titus Gordion

"Excellent. What would you like to start with?"

Titus Gordion

"This way, sir."

RiziaHistoryHub

Player_Romus

"Tell me about that impressive suit of armor."

Player_Romus

"Actually, I'm ready to move on."

Player_Romus

"I'm curious to know about... whatever *that* is."

Titus Gordion

"Very well."

Titus Gordion

"It was, however, supposedly used on suspected spies during the Rizian Succession."

Titus Gordion

"'Terador's Fury.' Its notoriety spans back several hundred years, just after the Empire of Valgos seized Pales from Rizia."

Titus Gordion

"After securing power in Monqiz, his dynasty maintained a stronghold over the city-state throughout the Markian era and, upon the foundation of the Kingdom of Rizia, assumed control over neighboring Valenqiris."

Hugo Toras

"Legend has it, this sword supposedly took off the head of the Valgos army's top general."

Player_Romus

"A bad day for him."

Titus Gordion

"That would be the armor of King Henricus Toras, the first ancestor from whom all members of your house are descended."

Player_Romus

"What interests me most about this story is the part about Pales being annexed from Rizia. That's what keeps me awake at night."

Titus Gordion

"But I'm sure you knew that already."

Hugo Toras

"Yes. However, if I may be so bold, Your Grace, there are valuable lessons to be learned from looking to Rizia's past -- lessons that could address present-day challenges, should they arise."

Titus Gordion

"Any items of particular interest?"

Hugo Toras

"If I may be so bold, Your Grace, there are valuable lessons to be learned from looking to Rizia's past -- lessons that could address present-day challenges, should they arise."

Narrator

We continued onward until we reached Captain Gordion's office on the far side of the hall. It too was adorned with a large collection of war memorabilia.

Narrator

Uncle Hugo sat on a sofa that looked to have been plucked from the 19th century.

Hugo Toras

"Don't mind if I do."

Player_Romus

"Standing suits me better."

Player_Romus

"No thanks. We won't be here long."

Player_Romus

"Drinking on the job? You should both be ashamed of yourselves."

Player_Romus

"Just a little bit. I've got to stay sharp for the rest of the day's activities."

Player_Romus

"It's a bit early, but what the hell?"

Player_Romus

"You had me at 'Would you care for some wine?'"

Narrator

The captain took out a bottle of wine from a cabinet.

Hugo Toras

"I'll have a glass."

Player_Romus

"Thanks, but no thanks. I only drink wine from 1892."

Narrator

Captain Gordion put the bottle away.

Hugo Toras

"And mine as well."

Hugo Toras

"I don't have an aversion to 1893, but I'll abstain as well. I wouldn't want to be the only one drinking."

Player_Romus

"Fantastic. I do hope this isn't the only bottle in existence."

Player_Romus

"This is absolutely awful. Take it away."

Titus Gordion

"Whatever makes you comfortable."

Titus Gordion

"Whatever suits you better."

Hugo Toras

"I actually kind of like it..."

Narrator

Titus took my glass away and set it elsewhere before returning.

Narrator

Titus placed the bottle elsewhere before he returned.

Titus Gordion

"Sorry to hear that. Next time, I'll open a different bottle."

Titus Gordion

"Unfortunately, this is my only one, but I'm sure there are others hidden away elsewhere in the kingdom."

Hugo Toras

"Too bad. I'm really enjoying this too."

Hugo Toras

"Keep me in the loop as well. I'm thoroughly enjoying this."

Player_Romus

"As the King of Rizia, I have many enemies. I wanted to make sure you're not one of them."

Player_Romus

"It was suggested by my uncle that I get to know you better. He seems to think that forging a personal relationship outside our working one will prove highly beneficial."

Titus Gordion

"I don't see why not. What would you like to know?"

Titus Gordion

"It's been quite some time since I was among the common people, Your Majesty."

Titus Gordion

"Certainly not, Your Majesty. Please, ask me anything."

Player_Romus

"Why don't you tell me more about yourself."

Player_Romus

"Let's hear more about the Golden Guard."

Titus Gordion

"Well, I was born and raised in Porte Drazon. My father was in the military while my mother took care of me and my siblings."

Titus Gordion

"I'd be honored. As you already know, every man here has sworn an oath to protect the royal household. We answer to no one else but you."

GoldenTitusHistoryHub

Player_Romus

"He gave his life for a good cause."

Titus Gordion

"For what it's worth, sir, he believed in the cause. He never turned against King Valero."

Titus Gordion

"He believed in it with all his heart. He never turned against King Valero."

Titus Gordion

"I had a fairly normal childhood until my father was killed during the operation to take back Pales."

Titus Gordion

"Needless to say, his death brought about a long period of financial instability. My mother did what she could, but it wasn't enough."

Hugo Toras

"How did you get by?"

Player_Romus

"Well, that explains your fisticuffs from earlier! How'd you do? Do well, I assume?"

Player_Romus

"Yes, yes... We've been over that already. Tell me something I don't already know."

Player_Romus

"And I am forever grateful. Please, continue."

Player_Romus

"'Private matters?' How intriguing. Please elaborate."

Player_Romus

"Oh, I'm definitely interested in hearing more."

Titus Gordion

"For king and country, Your Majesty."

Titus Gordion

"We do what we must to ensure the protection of the monarchy. And sometimes that requires us to extend beyond our typical duties."

Titus Gordion

"Let's just say... the public is better off not not knowing the types of operations we handle beyond security matters."

Player_Romus

"Speak plainly. I grow tired of your ambiguity."

Player_Romus

"Please continue. I want to know more."

Player_Romus

"You've definitely gotten my attention. Keep going."

Narrator

Titus hesitated a moment, casting a curious glance at Hugo as he did.

Hugo Toras

"Since their return, their dealing with such matters has been limited in scope, however, the potential to broaden their... *flexibility* is still there."

Player_Romus

"I'd heard rumors of such clandestine actions, but this is the first time I've received official confirmation."

Titus Gordion

"We only work within the confines given to us by the king. It's a matter of defining what those parameters are."

Titus Gordion

"Secretly is of the utmost importance to us."

Titus Gordion

"A long time ago, yes. But it was more to do with public relations. By deploying us to assist in disaster relief, the crown could demonstrate concern for the well-being of the local populous."

Player_Romus

"If we're so desperate we need the assistance of the Golden Guard to put out fires, we have far greater problems on our hands."

Player_Romus

"That's ridiculous. You can rest assured that I won't be sending you out on any firefighting excursions."

Player_Romus

"Well, then next time I hear of any kittens stuck in trees, I'll let you know."

Titus Gordion

"I'm actually allergic to cats, but I won't let that get in my way."

Hugo Toras

"I think that was a very productive meeting, if I do say so myself."

Narrator

Before long, Hugo and I left the armory and were making our way back through the palace courtyard.

Player_Romus

"I didn't ask for your opinion."

Hugo Toras

"I have no doubt that it will."

Hugo Toras

"It is my honor, Your Majesty."

Hugo Toras

"I look forward to providing you with further guidance."

Player_Romus

"Watch your words. Your obligations mean little in the face of my authority."

Player_Romus

"Fine. But the next time you feel compelled to give unsolicited advice, you may find yourself on the receiving end of unsolicited... *feedback*, if you will."

Player_Romus

"You're right. Please excuse my curtness. I welcome any and all advice you have to give."

Narrator

Hugo and I said our goodbyes and parted ways.

Narrator

I still wasn't fully sold on whether or not Titus could be trusted but satisfied knowing that my influence over him remained strong.

Hugo Toras

"Such collaboration will not only elevate but bring us closer to our goals."

Hugo Toras

"I prefer... realistically optimistic."

Player_Romus

"So sure of yourself, are you?"

Hugo Toras

"His Majesty's words are final."

Narrator

Hugo gave a slight nod.

Hugo Toras

"Not arrogant. Self-confident."

Narrator

Titus gave a heartfelt bow and left my company.

Narrator

Navigating through the armory once more, I eventually found my uncle in the vicinity of Titus' boxing match.

Narrator

I retraced my steps through the armory, and before long, I found myself back outside crossing the courtyard.

Hugo Toras

"There you are! I trust your discussion with Titus was productive?"

Player_Romus

"That's none of your concern."

Hugo Toras

"Your discretion is duly noted."

Hugo Toras

"I do hope you'll one day hold him in as high regard as I do."

Hugo Toras

"I'm pleased to hear it."

Player_Romus

"Your comprehensive explanation is appreciated."

Player_Romus

"Thanks for sharing, Titus."

Titus Gordion

"I'm glad I could provide you with further insight."

Titus Gordion

"I'll make sure of it."

Player_Romus

"That will be all, thank you."

Narrator

I left my uncle and caught up to Captain Gordion as he was stepping inside the building.

Titus Gordion

"Nevertheless the chance to fully restore our actions remains open."

Titus Gordion

"If there's anything else I can do for you, don't hesitate to ask."

Player_Romus

"Til next time."

Player_Romus

"Goodbye, Titus."

Narrator

I motioned to a broadsword prominently displayed in the center of the room. I assumed it's placement held particular significance.

Narrator

I pointed to an intricately adorned armored suit that stood out amongst the others.

Narrator

Player_Romus

"Yes. Most reassuring."

Player_Romus

"Hard to believe it was used at all."

"Not often. It was more to scare people, if anything."

"How lovely. Well, I hope its use produced positive results."

Titus Gordion

"It is indeed a sore spot in our history."

Titus Gordion

"To put it lightly..."

"But you knew that already, am I right?"

"I still have my reservation about whether or not he can be trusted."

"Okay, that's enough small talk. Let's shift this conversation to a more private setting."

"They also carried out arrests and even liquidation of individuals who posed a threat to the crown."

"Since the founding of the Golden Guard, long before your father reinstated them, they were known to engage in espionage."

Player_Romus

"Same. I like what you've done to the place."

Titus looked around, then turned back to me.

Titus Gordion

"Your government security forces seem to have a handle on the populace. But who has a handle on them?"

Titus Gordion

"I don't want to overstep my bounds so early into my employ. But I do believe the Azaros could pose a threat."

"Please don't worry His Majesty with such speculations, Captain Gordion. House Azaro and House Toras have been close allies since the War of Rizian Succession."

Player_Romus

Player_Romus

Titus Gordion
